# HerCare App Implementation Plan (Phase 7)

For Phase 7, we will bring the application to life by tackling two of the most requested features for highly polished apps: **Contextual Awareness** (Smart Insights) and **Accessibility** (Night Shift Theme).

## Proposed Changes

### 1. "Night Shift" Theme (Dark Mode)
Since this is a companion app for nurses who often work irregular night hours, a harsh bright screen can be jarring. 
- We will wire up the currently static "Night Shift" toggle inside `Settings.tsx`.
- We will establish mapped CSS variables in `index.css` via a `.night-shift-theme` class appended to the `<body>` element.
- This will swap the bright whites and lavender to rich, calming dark tones (deep plum/navy) when activated and persist it in local storage.

### 2. Smart Wellness Insights (`Home.tsx`)
We will read the data we started collecting in Phase 6 to provide a personalized, dynamic "AI" Insight card right on the Home Dashboard instead of static text.
- If hydration count `< 4`: "Insight: You were a bit behind on water yesterday. Try to grab a sip before 2 AM!"
- If mood `=== 'tired'`: "Insight: You logged feeling tired recently. Be gentle with yourself tonight."
- If everything is great: "Insight: You're on a great streak! Keep up the amazing work tonight."

